<p>When selecting a solar installer in Austin, prioritize companies with proper Texas licensing, including both electrical contractor licenses and solar-specific certifications from organizations like NABCEP (North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners). Look for installers with extensive local experience who understand Austin's specific permitting requirements and Austin Energy's interconnection procedures. Quality contractors should offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-12 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 5-10 years). Request multiple quotes, verify insurance coverage, and check references from recent Austin installations. Top-rated companies in the area typically maintain A+ Better Business Bureau ratings and provide detailed energy production estimates using local weather data and Austin Energy rate structures.</p>

